===Noun===
'''jute'''

#The coarse, strong fiber of the East [[Indian]] plant, Corchorus olitorius, used to make mats, paper, gunny cloth etc.
#The [[Germanic]] tribe that existed in modern-day [[Denmark]] that invaded England about the same time as the [[Angles]] and the [[Saxons]] in the beginning of the [[Middle Ages]], but were eventually either consumed culturally or driven out of the island.  Many [[historians]] believe a majority of [[Welsh]] culture derives, possibly, from Jute influence.
#A slang term, relatively new to the American lexicon, referring to one's promiscuity and often used as a gibberish element of exclamation.
#:<i>"Jute trash!" he said, having realized the futility of his efforts.</i>
